name: Patricia Griemsmann
text: Fast, quick, friendly, clean, I'm going back. Ingredients were fresh and t h e pizza cooks fast. We had meat lover and chicken and garlic. I've only had original crust, I hear the thin is excellent as well. Enjoy, keep an eye on it in the oven. I burnt it the fir SD t time we had it.

name: William Anderson
text: We have so far tried the garlic chicken pizza and the papas favorite (everything) pizza. Both were very, very good! I really like using the app after I get off of work on my way home. When I get there I just walk in and pick it up and take it home. We now have a weekly pizza night with Papa Murphyâ€™s Pizza!

name: Phyllis Leclair
text: Love their pizzas!  They almost never lack in toppings.  I also like the fact that I can cook them myself at home so when itâ€™s time to eat the pizza is hot.  We get original crust & it cooks up in about 10-12 minutes.  Most of their personnel is very pleasant!  Restaurant looks very clean.

name: Julie Shaw
text: This is a great pizza place. They have great deals on Tuesdays. All of their ingredients taste fresh and they add a lot of toppings. I reccomend trying it out. Just know that this is a take and bake and you have to bake it at home.

name: Pamela Doherty
text: We miss having this place by us and are super sad it closed. The staff was wonderful.

name: Patty Bellotte
text: We love the freshly made pizzas - especially on $10 Tuesdays!

name: Rick Gaspa
text: This restaurant is only a couple of years old. Immaculate and well maintained.  Veteran owned and operated. Very friendly staff. Great pizza. If you want a pizza prepared, baked and ready to eat, Papa Murphy's is not for you.  Papa Murphy's â€¦More

name: Carolee Eck
text: Always friendly, clean, and fast. Pizzas are great & the owner is always around & nice. Andi helped me today and she was super nice!

name: Tracy C.
text: Pizza is always delicious! The employees are great and they remember who you are and they are always friendlyðŸ˜Š they make you feel welcomed not an inconvenience!

name: steve01030
text: Good pizza.....great prices

name: Charles Stigger
text: Great customer service.  Team member adjusted order and made 1/4 of our pizza with heavy meat toppings.  Nice deal!

name: Lady Murasaki
text: You bake it at home so it's always fresh & hot!

name: Jan Nanning
text: Most disappointing, toppings look like they have been put through a good processor.  Taste ok while hot but awful when cold. First pizza I ever threw out.

name: Chell Chell
text: Great pizza, the manager does his job well

name: Richard Decoy
text: Love that I get texts of their daily discounts. Very convenient take and bake.

name: Andrew MacKenzie
text: Best take and bake Pizza there is, also better than any chain delivery option.

name: Stephanie Pecka
text: We love Papa Murphy's! They are also good on a Traeger! Yumm

name: John Ronnie Tippins
text: Great location and great pizza!

name: Blaine Foster
text: This is a good place to get pizza, take it home & bake it yourself. They have a punch card, after 10 times you earn major discounts.

name: Alexis Alcantar
text: We had high expectations from here and unfortunately they were not met. Perhaps we got the wrong pizza, but the sauce was very sour and tart. We got the Chicago double layered pizza. We ate half and the other half is in the fridge for days now.

name: Michael Mitchell
text: The pizza is great. I just don't uderstand why it costs so much when I do all of the cooking.

name: Pappy
text: Order was ready as promised

name: Cynthia Knight
text: First time, wasn't that impressed.

name: Trevor Miller
text: Always a great experience.

name: Deborah Edwards
text: Pizza made to order, pies are loaded with toppings.

name: Carmella Salvo
text: Awesome pizza!!
